fr.sorbonne_u.components.cyphy.plugins.devs.interfaces

Interface SupervisorPluginManagementI

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    SupervisorPluginI, SupervisorPluginManagementCI
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SupervisorPlugin, SupervisorPluginManagementConnector, SupervisorPluginManagementInboundPort, SupervisorPluginManagementOutboundPort

    public interface SupervisorPluginManagementI
    The interface SupervisorPluginManagementI declares the methods offered by the supervisor plug-in to the components holding them to create and connect simulation architectures.

    Description

    Invariant

     invariant      true

    Created on : 2018-06-20

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      void connectRootSimulatorComponent()
      connect this supervisor to the component C holding the root model in the simulation architecture it supervises and memorise the simulation plug-in management outbound port used to perform the connection and make C connect to the supervisor notification inbound port of this supervisor; this method is called by createSimulator.
      void createSimulator()

      • createSimulator

        void createSimulator()
              throws java.lang.Exception
        create the simulation architecture given the description already set in the plug-in.

        Description

        Main entry point to install a simulation architecture from the supervisor component. The architecture description must have been set priori to the call. The method will first connect the components participating in the simulation architecture (using the method connectRootSimulatorComponent and then will compose their simulation models using the method compose defined by the architecture descriptor.

        Contract

         pre    true            // no precondition.
 post   true            // no postcondition.
